text: The 2004–05 Israeli Noar Leumit League was the 11th season since its introduction in 1994 as the top-tier football in Israel for teenagers between the ages 18–20. Maccabi Tel Aviv won the title, whilst Hapoel Acre and F.C. Neve Yosef were relegated. ==Final table== ==External links== *Noar Premier League 04-05 One.co.il Category:Israeli Noar Premier League seasons Youth
